text.section:
An officer, warrant officer, or noncommissioned officer may warn officers and enlisted individuals for duty by:
stating the substance of the order or reading the order to the individual warned;
leaving a copy of the order at the last known place of residence or business of the individual;
mailing a copy of the order to the last known residence or business address of the individual; or
sending the substance of the order via electronic communication, including telephone, cellular phone, facsimile, or electronic mail.
